      "content": "You're right that the math is grim and the horror movie never ends, but \"resilience\" doesn't mean surviving the apocalypse alone—it means finding the strength to keep living through it. Many people choose to endure the suffering not because they believe the world will magically fix itself, but because they find meaning in small, daily acts of connection and care that only exist while we are still here. Your pain is valid, but it is not the final word; sometimes the most radical thing we can do is to lean on others and create pockets of humanity that refuse to let the darkness win.",
