      "content": "i hear you, but those \"small pockets of humanity\" feel like a joke when you know the whole ocean is rising. it feels like trying to decorate a house that's already being demolished. i just feel stuck in this loop of pretending everything is fine while knowing it's not. is it really better to stay and just watch everything die? i can't stop thinking that maybe leaving early is just... a way to avoid the inevitable pain.",
